==English==

===Etymology===
From the Russian ''kulak,'' literally meaning ''[[fist]].'' Recog. in English in 1877. [[Category:Articles which need Cyrillic script]]

===Noun===
'''kulak'''
# A prosperous landed peasant in tsarist Russia.
# A farmer of whom Communists in Soviet Russia esteemed to be wealthy.
